# SPU-13 Null Hysteresis Constraints: iCeSugar (iCE40UP5K)
# v3.1.33 "Virtual Induction Tuning"
# Objective: Physical mapping for Laminar Silence and Resonant Parasitics.

# --- 1. Resonant Clock Entry (Chiral Vortex) ---
# Pin 35 is the Global Clock input. We map it here to ensure the Sierpinski
# clock tree has a geometrically centered root.
set_io clk_resonant 35

# --- 2. Janus-Gate Differential Output (Tuned Drive Strength) ---
# We configure these pins for HIGH drive strength (48mA if supported, or max available)
# to aggressively drive the "Virtual Coil" of the twisted-pair trace.
# By matching the slew rate to the resonant frequency, we minimize edge-ringing
# and maximize the standing wave potential.
set_io -current 6 janus_pos 46
set_io -current 6 janus_neg 47

# --- 3. Manifold Status Indicators (Spectral Balance) ---
# The RGB LED is used to visualize the internal rotation state.
# Red = Axis A (Invariant), Green = Axis B/C/D (Orbit), Blue = Phase Lock.
set_io led_red   39
set_io led_green 40
set_io led_blue  41

# --- 4. Command & Control (Surd-Bridge) ---
# The UART interface allows the Rust Surd-Converter to drive the core.
# Mapped to the dedicated FTDI pins for minimal latency.
set_io uart_tx 10
set_io uart_rx 9

# --- 5. Virtual Induction Parameters ---
# We treat the trace parasitics not as noise, but as a Laminar Buffer.
# These constraints ensure the IO blocks act as "Field Shapers."
# (Note: Drive strength values are specific to iCE40 IO Bank capabilities)
